cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about a machine learning technique called model-agnostic meta-learning (MAML) and its extension called Alpha MAML. The paper discusses the application of MAML in various learning tasks such as classification, regression, and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses the Omniglot database, which is a popular dataset in computer vision, suggesting that cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of policy gradients in reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the stability of the training process, which is relevant to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well.
